The flat on the front underside of the frame and the bottom of the trigger guard just behind it are marked “183691”. The inside surface of the loading gate is marked with the assembly number “766”. Barrel Length: >18” Sights / Optics: The front sight is a tall blade fixed to the top of the barrel. The rear sight is a “U” groove in the top strap. Stock Configuration & Condition: The stocks are two piece smooth walnut with a lacquered finish. The buttstock is fancy walnut with fiddleback and burl patterns with a straight grip and a blued crescent shaped buttplate. The forend is 5 ½” long, rounded and screwed to the underside of the barrel just in front of the ejector rod. The buttstock shows several light handling marks on the left side of the wrist and several more on its left side, with a single light mark on the right side of the wrist and a few light marks in the comb. There are repaired crack at the top front of the buttstock on both sides of the upper tang – these were probably inserts inlet into the buttstock to match the contour of the upper tang. The forend has a repaired crack on its right side that runs nearly the full length of the forend. The LOP measures 13 1/8” from the front of the trigger to the back of the buttplate. postcontent: I've got an extra reservation for Medical Prep 101 and 201 with Patriot Nurse on April 9 + 10.  The class is going to be in Chadds Ford.  I've already made arrangements that the registration is transferrable.I can't use it, so I'm offering it at about half off.  Asking $300 obo.Course Description: In this jam-packed 8 hour class, we will dive into diseases and injuries most likely to strike in a long-term disaster scenario and in everyday life, too!  Our students comment that this class is like drinking from a medical fire hose of knowledge.  Come well rested and ready to rocket into a dynamic training and learning environment!In addition to strengthening our knowledge base, we will also take regular breaks for application.  Skills sessions will include physical assessment, taking blood pressure, post-mortem care, drug calculation, austere rehydration (when you don’t have IV fluids), and much more!  The student will leave this class equipped with the knowledge and skills to better safeguard their loved ones’ health whatever life may throw at them! You will receive a full course manual with your tuition fee.  Wear layers and loose fitting clothes to class -- you will be practicing hands-on application.  Problem-solving, critical thinking, and dynamic adaptation are key components of this course.  So come prepared to work, grow, and learn!  Bring an open mind and a teachable attitude. No prior medical training is necessary :)Medical Prep 201:  Course Description:  We pick up in 201 where we left off in 101.  For retention, we will have a brief recap of 101, and then jump headlong into deeper physical assessment, refining our skills and furthering our knowledge.  Total body physical assessment and problem solving will inform our medical preparedness approach.We will delve into a critical and HIGHLY under-addressed area of preparedness – psychological challenges.   We will investigate how a major disaster will affect people’s minds and hearts, causing significant depression, anxiety, and fear.  Learning how to assess, prevent and take care of these problems is INTEGRAL to a well-rounded medical survival plan.  Additionally, we will discuss options for pain control when the medicine runs out, and how to care for people who are suffering from physical and emotional pain.Women’s health, STD’s, and BIRTH will also be covered extensively in this class, with skills sessions built around assisting in a birth and preparing for possible complications such miscarriage, excessive bleeding, babies that don’t breathe, and breech birth.As a final component, we will synergize our knowledge into developing a camp layout and design that facilitates health and wellness of everyone staying at a bug out or retreat.  Blending components of 101 and 201, we’ll practice solving issues and challenges of water shortages, human waste management, and the proper disposal of human bodies.

title: For Sale:  .308 Ruger GSR + Extras
postcontent: I am selling my Ruger Gunsite Scout with everything that came in the box except the manual. I have a Leopold FX-II 2.5x28mm Fixed Intermediate Eye Relief Scope. With the scope set forward on the rails you do not need to close both eyes to clearly see the crosshairs allowing you to stay aware of your entire field of view. It has an extra 5 round polymer mag with dust cover in addition to the 10 round aluminum mag that came with it. It has a padded shoulder strap included. I also have a Laser Ammo cartridge with .308 adapter and target that allows for dry fire practice at anywhere from 10ft to however far out you can hit such a small target. It is great for saving money on ammo. I also have the adapter to make the Laser Ammo cartridge so it will work with a 12guage shotgun if you like to practice your center of mass shots. The cartridge itself is made to work with 9mm guns. Although it will not cycle the slide, so a DA pistol or pump shotgun is best. I have a pack of batteries that are a fraction of what Laser Ammo charges and works fine, I believe I have about 54 of them left, so don't worry about running out of juice. It is a great value as all of the Laser Ammo parts together would cost around $300 realistically depending on who you get it through and it is really the best laser ammo. I did quite a bit of research on it. Despite all this if you don't want it, I will deduct $150 off the total price.I have also included 15 168 grain rounds, sufficient for hunting or blowing up small objects. I would prefer to sell this all together for the price listed, but to leave off the laser ammo if requested as I am sure I can come up with a use for it. Anyone who knows this rifle knows the scope that I have on it was practically made for it, it is sufficient for hunting and good for low light conditions where zoom scopes are harder to use. I do not want to leave the scope off this rifle as I do not have another use for it. Everything is in like-new condition, no scratches scuffs or significant use. I has had around 30 rounds put through it, I mostly used it with the laser ammo for dry fire practice which does not hurt the firing pin, as the round acts like a snap cap.I will meet you in person anywhere in the Atlanta area if you are a serious buyer, and cash only.
